<li><a href="http://3quarksdaily.blogs.com/3quarksdaily/2005/05/monday_musing_s.html" class="external text" title="http://3quarksdaily.blogs.com/3quarksdaily/2005/05/monday_musing_s.html" rel="nofollow">Stevinus, Galileo, and Thought Experiments</a> Short essay by S. Abbas Raza of <a href="http://3quarksdaily.com" class="external text" title="http://3quarksdaily.com" rel="nofollow"><i>3 Quarks Daily</i></a></li>
<li><a href="http://www.thoughtexperimentgenerator.co.uk/" class="external text" title="http://www.thoughtexperimentgenerator.co.uk/" rel="nofollow">Thought experiment generator</a>, an entertaining visual aid to running your own thought experiment</li>
<li>Articles on <a href="http://philsci-archive.pitt.edu/view/subjects/thought-experiments.html" class="external text" title="http://philsci-archive.pitt.edu/view/subjects/thought-experiments.html" rel="nofollow"><i>Thought Experiments</i></a> in the <i>PhilSci Archive</i>, an electronic archive for preprints in the philosophy of science.</li>
<li>The <a href="http://cleanslate.editboard.com/" class="external text" title="http://cleanslate.editboard.com/" rel="nofollow">Clean Slate Society Forums</a> "If we could start again, from a clean slate, knowing what we know today, what would we do differently?"</li>
</ul>


